<br>
I'm sure most that have played the cats in Shadeweavers have noticed NO RENT armor drops off them sometimes, to make these into wearable armor that isn't NO RENT follow these steps.<br>
<br>
First, you must go on a killing spree of hoppers and saureks.  Collect as many <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   a needle thin claw</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->'s as possible, and also collect all the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   a damaged hopperhide</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->'s as you can.<br>
<br>
Try to get the needle thin claws in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  quantities of four</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, this is for a quest.  Go to the building that is opposite the bank outside in Shadeweaver, looks just the same, with a male Vah Shir tailor.  Turn in 4 of the claws to recieve <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   a claw needle</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, these <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   are</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> stackable.<br>
<br>
Now, go out and hunt lesser shades after stocking up on damaged hopperhides and claw needles, collecting ALL of the NO RENT armor that you pick up off them.<br>
<br>
After you get a piece or pieces, go to the tailor again and buy a sketch for the type of armor you have that is NO RENT.  Combine, in your beginners tailor kit or a store bought one, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   1 damaged hopperhide and the sketch</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in the kit to create Tattered (whatever piece) armor.<br>
<br>
Take the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Tattered armor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, along with the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   NO RENT armor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, and combine them in a kit <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   ALONG WITH a single claw needle</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (the result of the 4 needle thin claws to tailor, it is stackable)<br>
<br>
This will result in armor that is a MAGIC ITEM, not NO RENT and has same AC as the NO RENT armor, plus 1 SV Magic.<br>
<br>
To get tailoring up just continue making tattered and than move your way up as your skill increases.  At level 25 skill I successfully created 2 Shaded Hopperhide Tunics.<br>
<br>
